ia_National_Park_August_2015.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f6/Bar_Island_%28Maine%29.jpg/1280px-Bar_Island_%28Maine%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f6/Bar_Island_%28Maine%29.jpg","cap":"Bar Island (Maine)","desc":"Bar Island, an uninhabited tidal island in Bar Harbor, Maine. It's part of the Acadia National Park.","credit":"Quintin Soloviev · CC BY 4.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Bar_Island_(Maine).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/Acadia_All_American_Road_-_A_Bar_Harbor_Church_in_the_Fall_-_NARA_-_7716802.jpg/1280px-Acadia_All_American_Road_-_A_Bar_Harbor_Church_in_the_Fall_-_NARA_-_7716802.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c4/Acadia_All_American_Road_-_A_Bar_Harbor_Church_in_the_Fall_-_NARA_-_7716802.jpg","cap":"Acadia All American Road A Bar Harbor Church in the Fall","desc":"Leafless trees frame this photo of a white church in Bar Harbor. Location: Maine (44.388° N 68.206° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Dennis Adams","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Acadia_All_American_Road_-_A_Bar_Harbor_Church_in_the_Fall_-_NARA_-_7716802.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Acadia_All_American_Road_-_Acadia_National_Park_Architecture_-_NARA_-_7716807.jpg/1280px-Acadia_All_American_Road_-_Acadia_National_Park_Architecture_-_NARA_-_7716807.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/16/Acadia_All_American_Road_-_Acadia_National_Park_Architecture_-_NARA_-_7716807.jpg","cap":"Acadia All American Road Acadia National Park Architecture","desc":"Fine landscaping surrounds a carriage road house in Acadia National Park. Location: Acadia National Park, Maine (44.342° N 68.273° W) Status: Public domain. Photos taken by Bill Compton","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Acadia_All_American_Ro